//     {label:'Projectile motion & launch angle optimisation',concept:'Motion',related:'Forces, Energy, Vectors',lp:'Thinkers, Knowledgeable',atl:'Thinking, Research',aoCrit:'SL/HL Paper 1 & 2 — Topic 2: Mechanics',scene:'A side-view ballistic range — variable-angle launch ramp on the left, target zones at various distances. Projectile arc traces in real time. Separate horizontal and vertical velocity component arrows animate. Time-of-flight countdown displays.',sliders:['Launch angle θ degrees (0=0° — horizontal → 4=90° — vertical)','Initial speed u m/s (0=5 m/s → 4=50 m/s)','Air resistance coefficient (0=Vacuum → 4=High drag)','Launch height m (0=Ground level → 4=20m elevated)'],resources:['Horizontal range m (variable)','Maximum height m (variable)','Time of flight s (variable)','Target zone hit (variable)','Kinetic energy at landing J (variable)'],explain:'Students find the optimal launch angle (45° in vacuum, less with air resistance) through experimental rounds, discovering the mathematical relationship empirically before checking against kinematic equations.',real:'Artillery shell ballistic trajectories, Mars Perseverance rover EDL, Golf ball dimple aerodynamics, Javelin throw biomechanics'},
